1
00:00:24,510 --> 00:00:25,510
You came all the way

2
00:00:25,510 --> 00:00:26,600
to give me a commendation?

3
00:00:28,280 --> 00:00:28,960
No.

4
00:00:29,280 --> 00:00:31,480
I was here on business.
Just happened to be passing by.

5
00:00:31,870 --> 00:00:32,600
Here on business?

6
00:00:33,024 --> 00:00:35,280
=Cases Between Us=
And you happened to stop by for this?

7
00:00:35,980 --> 00:00:37,380
=Episode 24=

8
00:00:37,390 --> 00:00:38,000
Wait.

9
00:00:38,990 --> 00:00:40,160
You suddenly came to my school.

10
00:00:40,176 --> 00:00:41,376
Did Wan'er say something to you?

11
00:00:41,390 --> 00:00:42,920
Most people

12
00:00:42,920 --> 00:00:43,840
only see

13
00:00:43,840 --> 00:00:45,030
what they expect to see.

14
00:00:45,710 --> 00:00:47,200
But there's so much more to you

15
00:00:47,200 --> 00:00:48,110
than that.

16
00:00:50,220 --> 00:00:52,140
(Certificate of Commendation
to Zhao Shaoshang)

17
00:00:55,200 --> 00:00:56,030
Can one certificate

18
00:00:56,320 --> 00:00:58,000
erase all those rumors?

19
00:00:58,710 --> 00:00:59,710
Even my dad says

20
00:01:00,110 --> 00:01:00,840
that without him

21
00:01:00,840 --> 00:01:01,710
covering for me...

22
00:01:04,064 --> 00:01:04,870
Where are we going?

23
00:01:04,870 --> 00:01:05,640
I'm hungry.

24
00:01:05,640 --> 00:01:06,310
Let's eat.

25
00:01:07,070 --> 00:01:08,280
I still have class.

26
00:01:10,590 --> 00:01:12,150
You have to save me.

27
00:01:12,350 --> 00:01:13,310
Otherwise,

28
00:01:13,540 --> 00:01:14,740
I'll tell the police

29
00:01:14,740 --> 00:01:15,840
everything.

30
00:01:15,840 --> 00:01:17,120
Go right ahead.

31
00:01:19,680 --> 00:01:21,310
The pharmaceutical factory

32
00:01:21,310 --> 00:01:23,000
only funded your research on new drugs.

33
00:01:23,230 --> 00:01:25,350
No one told you to abuse those children.

34
00:01:25,350 --> 00:01:27,840
Every medicine has to be tested.

35
00:01:27,840 --> 00:01:29,120
That's science.

36
00:01:34,790 --> 00:01:36,280
Aren't you a priest?

37
00:01:36,992 --> 00:01:38,760
Why are you talking to me about science?

38
00:01:40,350 --> 00:01:41,510
Did you lose your faith in God?

39
00:01:45,920 --> 00:01:47,000
You didn't come

40
00:01:48,350 --> 00:01:50,430
to say goodbye, did you?

41
00:01:55,590 --> 00:01:59,510
Where did you hide your research notes?

42
00:02:02,840 --> 00:02:03,560
Just as I thought.

43
00:02:08,470 --> 00:02:10,030
Do you think I'm stupid?

44
00:02:10,176 --> 00:02:12,672
I can have your sentence commuted to
a suspended death sentence.

45
00:02:13,310 --> 00:02:14,960
Then you'll be released in six months.

46
00:02:15,750 --> 00:02:16,960
Get it now?

47
00:02:20,030 --> 00:02:21,400
Don't listen to him.

48
00:02:21,630 --> 00:02:22,520
It's hopeless.

49
00:02:24,120 --> 00:02:26,400
You're being executed
first thing tomorrow morning.

50
00:02:26,400 --> 00:02:27,560
I'll personally oversee it.

51
00:02:28,000 --> 00:02:28,800
Unless

52
00:02:29,400 --> 00:02:30,190
he gets

53
00:02:30,190 --> 00:02:32,150
a presidential pardon,

54
00:02:32,840 --> 00:02:34,280
you're as good as dead.

55
00:02:39,840 --> 00:02:41,590
How do you know I can't?

56
00:02:43,150 --> 00:02:44,590
This case has gotten huge.

57
00:02:44,624 --> 00:02:47,408
(Father Pans Abuse Children)
Over twenty newspapers have covered it.

58
00:02:48,240 --> 00:02:49,680
Public outrage is boiling over.

59
00:02:50,000 --> 00:02:50,840
Secretary Xu,

60
00:02:51,630 --> 00:02:53,150
at least in my opinion,

61
00:02:53,150 --> 00:02:54,710
any politician with half a brain

62
00:02:54,960 --> 00:02:55,590
wouldn't risk

63
00:02:55,590 --> 00:02:56,750
his own life

64
00:02:56,750 --> 00:02:58,150
to save a complete stranger.

65
00:02:59,240 --> 00:03:00,080
Don't you agree?

66
00:03:03,280 --> 00:03:05,840
You're leaving us no way out?

67
00:03:06,000 --> 00:03:07,910
You're the ones
who've cornered yourselves.

68
00:03:08,190 --> 00:03:09,710
You broke the law

69
00:03:09,710 --> 00:03:11,120
for a few dirty coins.

70
00:03:11,120 --> 00:03:13,240
Do you think
the police department is yours?

71
00:03:20,400 --> 00:03:20,840
Fine.

72
00:03:21,470 --> 00:03:22,150
Chief Yuan,

73
00:03:23,000 --> 00:03:25,030
I know you're fearless.

74
00:03:27,080 --> 00:03:31,030
You may not care about your own life,

75
00:03:33,120 --> 00:03:33,910
but I don't believe

76
00:03:33,910 --> 00:03:35,470
there's no one else in this world

77
00:03:35,800 --> 00:03:37,710
you care about.

78
00:03:38,630 --> 00:03:39,840
We'll see about that.

79
00:03:48,080 --> 00:03:48,800
Secretary Xu.

80
00:03:52,360 --> 00:03:53,120
Stop looking.

81
00:03:53,800 --> 00:03:54,840
No one's coming to save you.

82
00:03:56,360 --> 00:03:57,360
I'm not going anywhere

83
00:03:57,910 --> 00:03:59,120
before the execution.

84
00:04:05,460 --> 00:04:09,060
(The Fake Priest
Finally Brought to Justice)

85
00:04:15,800 --> 00:04:17,830
Do you know who's behind Secretary Xu?

86
00:04:19,360 --> 00:04:19,920
Who?

87
00:04:21,630 --> 00:04:22,310
General Chen.

88
00:04:26,190 --> 00:04:27,430
My father's sworn enemy.

89
00:04:29,040 --> 00:04:29,680
On the surface,

90
00:04:29,680 --> 00:04:31,370
Secretary Xu works
for the State Council,

91
00:04:31,420 --> 00:04:33,580
but he's General Chen's mouthpiece.

92
00:04:34,020 --> 00:04:35,780
General Chen was once badly wounded.

93
00:04:36,860 --> 00:04:38,980
If he hadn't coordinated
with a foreign doctor,

94
00:04:38,980 --> 00:04:41,020
he'd have died.

95
00:04:41,620 --> 00:04:42,500
Remember when

96
00:04:42,500 --> 00:04:44,700
we were ambushed
outside Ji'an Apothecary?

97
00:04:44,900 --> 00:04:46,780
I told you
they were using military rounds.

98
00:04:47,260 --> 00:04:48,020
I'm wondering...

99
00:04:49,340 --> 00:04:51,380
Could it be connected
to your mother's death?

100
00:04:51,424 --> 00:04:53,060
They know you're looking into the truth,

101
00:04:53,300 --> 00:04:54,540
so they keep getting in your way.

102
00:04:57,540 --> 00:04:58,460
Too bad

103
00:04:59,020 --> 00:05:01,140
we didn't catch their contact last time.

104
00:05:01,780 --> 00:05:02,660
The trail went cold.

105
00:05:05,008 --> 00:05:06,660
Didn't you think
the day we arrested Pans

106
00:05:06,660 --> 00:05:07,580
was strange?

107
00:05:09,380 --> 00:05:10,140
Wen

108
00:05:10,620 --> 00:05:11,980
is only around ten.

109
00:05:12,580 --> 00:05:13,140
How could she

110
00:05:13,140 --> 00:05:14,500
fight off a grown man?

111
00:05:14,980 --> 00:05:15,860
Right.

112
00:05:15,860 --> 00:05:16,780
That did seem odd.

113
00:05:17,740 --> 00:05:19,580
Wan'er talked to her

114
00:05:19,580 --> 00:05:20,820
at the orphanage.

115
00:05:22,000 --> 00:05:23,540
She said she took some pills that day.

116
00:05:24,340 --> 00:05:25,220
The Longevity Pills?

117
00:05:25,460 --> 00:05:26,100
No.

118
00:05:26,160 --> 00:05:27,440
She couldn't afford those.

119
00:05:28,100 --> 00:05:29,660
She said they were Strength Pills.

120
00:05:31,980 --> 00:05:33,300
Just another street scam.

121
00:05:33,300 --> 00:05:34,288
They're sold everywhere.

122
00:05:34,340 --> 00:05:35,680
How could they be that powerful?

123
00:05:36,780 --> 00:05:37,940
Where did she get them?

124
00:05:39,100 --> 00:05:41,300
She said she bought
them from the street.

125
00:05:41,620 --> 00:05:43,500
The package
had the character "Zhang" on it.

126
00:05:44,140 --> 00:05:44,980
Do you think

127
00:05:46,260 --> 00:05:46,980
they could contain

128
00:05:46,980 --> 00:05:48,060
methamphetamine?

129
00:05:48,900 --> 00:05:50,940
Madam Zhang sold the Longevity Pills

130
00:05:50,940 --> 00:05:53,300
because she was laundering money
for people above her.

131
00:05:55,100 --> 00:05:56,860
But these Strength Pills...

132
00:05:57,540 --> 00:05:58,540
I don't think so.

133
00:06:00,260 --> 00:06:01,580
- Great!
- Great!

134
00:06:03,740 --> 00:06:05,740
- Bravo!
- Bravo!

135
00:06:05,820 --> 00:06:07,300
- Excellent!
- Excellent!

136
00:06:07,860 --> 00:06:08,580
Young Master,

137
00:06:08,580 --> 00:06:09,420
that's incredible!

138
00:06:09,740 --> 00:06:11,220
- Great!
- Great!

139
00:06:11,500 --> 00:06:13,300
- Bravo!
- Bravo!

140
00:06:15,220 --> 00:06:16,020
Zhao Cai.

141
00:06:16,300 --> 00:06:16,980
Let's go.

142
00:06:17,620 --> 00:06:19,780
- Excellent!
- Excellent!

143
00:06:24,980 --> 00:06:25,500
Come.

144
00:06:25,500 --> 00:06:26,820
(Ironman Zhang)
Take a look.

145
00:06:26,820 --> 00:06:29,780
Ironman Zhang is going
to bend the bow.

146
00:06:30,032 --> 00:06:31,552
I have a man with real skills.

147
00:06:31,584 --> 00:06:33,580
Since it's getting late,
and we've got a good crowd,

148
00:06:33,580 --> 00:06:35,300
time for the main event!

149
00:06:35,300 --> 00:06:37,500
- Yes!
- Yes!

150
00:06:40,620 --> 00:06:43,260
(Zhang Dalu)

151
00:06:45,580 --> 00:06:46,720
Go.

152
00:06:48,180 --> 00:06:49,660
(Douding)
Take a Strength Pill.

153
00:07:15,020 --> 00:07:15,580
Bravo!

154
00:07:24,100 --> 00:07:25,220
- Bravo!
- Bravo!

155
00:07:26,060 --> 00:07:27,340
- Excellent!
- Excellent!

156
00:07:28,176 --> 00:07:29,250
These are the miracle pills

157
00:07:29,296 --> 00:07:30,940
passed down
by the Zhang troupe's master,

158
00:07:30,940 --> 00:07:31,700
Strength Pills.

159
00:07:32,060 --> 00:07:33,860
Take them orally to build strength,

160
00:07:33,860 --> 00:07:35,700
or apply them to ease bruises.

161
00:07:36,500 --> 00:07:37,660
Buy two, get one free today.

162
00:07:37,660 --> 00:07:38,860
One pill for one silver coin.

163
00:07:38,860 --> 00:07:40,660
Three for two.

164
00:07:41,060 --> 00:07:42,100
Try them today.

165
00:07:42,100 --> 00:07:44,260
Visit us again if you like.

166
00:07:44,460 --> 00:07:45,220
I want one.

167
00:07:45,280 --> 00:07:46,330
- Here you go.
- Come on.

168
00:07:46,352 --> 00:07:47,860
Thank you.

169
00:07:48,464 --> 00:07:50,272
I'll take two silver coins' worth.

170
00:07:51,380 --> 00:07:52,100
Young Master Zhao?

171
00:07:52,100 --> 00:07:53,460
What brings you here?

172
00:07:54,420 --> 00:07:55,700
How did you end up with them?

173
00:07:55,900 --> 00:07:57,180
Dalu took me in.

174
00:07:57,940 --> 00:07:59,140
Give me two.

175
00:08:00,020 --> 00:08:00,500
Here.

176
00:08:00,660 --> 00:08:01,500
I, Ironman Zhang,

177
00:08:01,820 --> 00:08:03,860
will show everyone another trick.

178
00:08:04,100 --> 00:08:05,740
Chest Crushing Stone.

179
00:08:05,740 --> 00:08:06,460
- Bravo!
- Bravo!

180
00:08:11,660 --> 00:08:13,060
Ladies and gentlemen,

181
00:08:13,060 --> 00:08:14,460
watch closely.

182
00:08:14,460 --> 00:08:15,660
You won't see this

183
00:08:15,660 --> 00:08:16,980
anywhere else.

184
00:08:17,820 --> 00:08:18,940
Watch carefully!

185
00:08:25,420 --> 00:08:26,380
- Great!
- Great!

186
00:08:26,550 --> 00:08:28,580
- Bravo!
- Bravo!

187
00:08:28,980 --> 00:08:32,460
- Excellent!
- Excellent!

188
00:08:33,340 --> 00:08:33,940
Bravo!

189
00:08:41,180 --> 00:08:42,340
Dalu!

190
00:08:42,700 --> 00:08:43,420
What's wrong, Dalu?

191
00:08:43,420 --> 00:08:43,980
Dalu!

192
00:08:43,980 --> 00:08:44,500
Zhang!

193
00:08:44,500 --> 00:08:45,140
Get a cart.

194
00:08:45,140 --> 00:08:46,220
- Take him to South City Clinic.
- Are you okay, Dalu?

195
00:08:46,220 --> 00:08:47,020
Go!

196
00:08:48,420 --> 00:08:48,860
Zhang!

197
00:08:48,860 --> 00:08:49,540
- Dalu!
- Zhang!

198
00:08:49,540 --> 00:08:50,300
Zhang!

199
00:08:54,060 --> 00:08:56,780
(Zhang)

200
00:08:56,780 --> 00:09:00,460
(Emergency Room)

201
00:09:03,300 --> 00:09:04,860
Oh, no.

202
00:09:05,580 --> 00:09:06,900
Will he be fine?

203
00:09:06,900 --> 00:09:07,540
He'll be fine.

204
00:09:07,540 --> 00:09:08,620
Trust me.

205
00:09:08,620 --> 00:09:09,300
He'll be fine.

206
00:09:09,580 --> 00:09:10,500
He definitely will.

207
00:09:12,660 --> 00:09:13,780
How is he?

208
00:09:15,380 --> 00:09:16,340
You can come in now.

209
00:09:23,140 --> 00:09:23,780
Dalu.

210
00:09:24,020 --> 00:09:25,620
Dalu!

211
00:09:27,940 --> 00:09:28,660
Liuzi,

212
00:09:28,860 --> 00:09:29,940
take Douding home.

213
00:09:30,500 --> 00:09:30,900
Dalu.

214
00:09:30,900 --> 00:09:32,690
Get a couple of men
to carry Dalu's body back.

215
00:09:32,700 --> 00:09:33,980
Right. Let's take him home first.

216
00:09:33,980 --> 00:09:34,340
Let's go.

217
00:09:34,340 --> 00:09:34,780
Douding.

218
00:09:34,780 --> 00:09:35,380
Behave, Douding.

219
00:09:35,380 --> 00:09:36,500
Dalu!

220
00:09:36,500 --> 00:09:37,300
Be good, Douding.

221
00:09:37,300 --> 00:09:38,100
Be good, girl.

222
00:09:38,100 --> 00:09:38,660
Come on.

223
00:09:50,740 --> 00:09:53,300
(Morgue)

224
00:09:59,580 --> 00:10:03,300
(Rest Stop, Inn)

225
00:10:43,180 --> 00:10:44,060
What is it?

226
00:10:44,220 --> 00:10:45,420
It's the middle of the night.

227
00:10:51,500 --> 00:10:52,260
Dalu!

228
00:10:52,260 --> 00:10:53,380
Shh.

229
00:10:54,340 --> 00:10:55,660
Can you be quiet?

230
00:11:14,260 --> 00:11:15,260
Dalu!

231
00:11:15,780 --> 00:11:16,620
Dalu!

232
00:11:19,088 --> 00:11:20,736
If you're not sleeping, get out of here.

233
00:11:20,780 --> 00:11:21,460
Little beggar.

234
00:11:21,460 --> 00:11:21,980
Stop.

235
00:11:22,620 --> 00:11:23,660
He's hitting me!

236
00:11:23,660 --> 00:11:24,500
Still running?

237
00:11:25,420 --> 00:11:25,820
Run again!

238
00:11:25,820 --> 00:11:26,820
I'll beat you to death!

239
00:11:26,848 --> 00:11:27,500
Get back here!

240
00:11:30,020 --> 00:11:31,100
(Jingshi Police Department)

241
00:11:31,100 --> 00:11:31,860
Stop!

242
00:11:32,620 --> 00:11:34,500
How dare you hit her
outside the police station?

243
00:11:34,500 --> 00:11:35,940
Officer! Please help me!

244
00:11:35,940 --> 00:11:37,180
Let go first.

245
00:11:37,180 --> 00:11:37,740
I can't.

246
00:11:37,740 --> 00:11:38,820
He'll beat me to death.

247
00:11:39,060 --> 00:11:40,260
Don't slander me.

248
00:11:40,500 --> 00:11:40,940
Look.

249
00:11:41,460 --> 00:11:42,340
She bit me.

250
00:11:42,672 --> 00:11:43,700
What's all the shouting?

251
00:11:44,100 --> 00:11:44,780
Chief Yuan.

252
00:11:45,780 --> 00:11:46,380
Chief Yuan!

253
00:11:46,380 --> 00:11:47,500
Chief Yuan, help me.

254
00:11:48,460 --> 00:11:49,300
You know me?

255
00:11:49,300 --> 00:11:50,460
Young Master Zhao said that

256
00:11:50,460 --> 00:11:52,700
if I'm ever in danger,
I should come here and find you.

257
00:11:53,780 --> 00:11:54,820
He also said

258
00:11:54,820 --> 00:11:56,620
you're a true hero of Jingshi.

259
00:11:56,688 --> 00:11:57,580
No one else would care

260
00:11:57,580 --> 00:11:59,488
about a little beggar,
but you definitely would.

261
00:11:59,504 --> 00:12:00,980
When did I ever call him a hero?

262
00:12:01,360 --> 00:12:03,660
You said he's capable
and stands up for what's right.

263
00:12:03,780 --> 00:12:04,820
Isn't that a hero?

264
00:12:05,296 --> 00:12:06,660
If you admire me that much,

265
00:12:08,460 --> 00:12:09,260
say it to my face.

266
00:12:09,260 --> 00:12:10,784
Don't listen to her. She's making it up.

267
00:12:11,020 --> 00:12:11,700
I'm not.

268
00:12:11,700 --> 00:12:12,700
Quiet.

269
00:12:12,700 --> 00:12:13,300
Stand there.

270
00:12:14,336 --> 00:12:15,540
Why were you hitting her?

271
00:12:15,980 --> 00:12:17,180
I wasn't.

272
00:12:17,540 --> 00:12:19,860
My master just wanted
to ask her a few questions.

273
00:12:20,380 --> 00:12:21,580
And she bit me and ran.

274
00:12:21,700 --> 00:12:22,140
Look.

275
00:12:22,780 --> 00:12:23,220
Enough.

276
00:12:23,408 --> 00:12:24,544
What did you want to ask?

277
00:12:25,100 --> 00:12:25,380
Well...

278
00:12:25,380 --> 00:12:26,500
It's about Dalu.

279
00:12:29,136 --> 00:12:30,800
What happened to him yesterday?

280
00:12:32,660 --> 00:12:33,460
He died.

281
00:12:43,220 --> 00:12:44,020
How did he die?

282
00:12:45,180 --> 00:12:47,420
Dalu was performing
the chest-breaking act.

283
00:12:47,488 --> 00:12:49,632
He coughed up blood
after taking one hammer blow.

284
00:12:49,740 --> 00:12:51,420
We took him to the clinic,

285
00:12:51,584 --> 00:12:52,860
but they couldn't save him.

286
00:12:52,860 --> 00:12:53,740
He died.

287
00:12:58,820 --> 00:12:59,980
What did you want with her?

288
00:13:01,860 --> 00:13:04,180
She'd been telling everyone

289
00:13:04,580 --> 00:13:06,380
she saw Zhang Dalu
come back alive last night.

290
00:13:07,260 --> 00:13:08,860
My master just wanted to know

291
00:13:09,100 --> 00:13:12,460
whether he had come back.

292
00:13:20,500 --> 00:13:21,860
What does that have to do

293
00:13:22,420 --> 00:13:24,100
with your master?

294
00:13:25,808 --> 00:13:27,420
Master Hu said
he was going to kill Dalu.

295
00:13:27,420 --> 00:13:28,420
Don't talk nonsense!

296
00:13:36,370 --> 00:13:38,220
It was just a little dispute.

297
00:13:41,900 --> 00:13:43,340
But Dalu and Master Hu...

298
00:13:43,340 --> 00:13:43,900
Hey, you!

299
00:13:43,900 --> 00:13:44,860
Are you out of your mind?

300
00:13:46,060 --> 00:13:46,700
Behave!

301
00:13:49,060 --> 00:13:49,620
It's fine.

302
00:13:50,140 --> 00:13:51,100
Yuan will protect you.

303
00:13:51,100 --> 00:13:51,780
Go on.

304
00:13:52,620 --> 00:13:54,020
What did Zhang Dalu do to Master Hu?

305
00:13:58,112 --> 00:13:59,888
He had an affair with Master Hu's wife.

306
00:14:07,827 --> 00:14:10,340
And broke one of his arms.

307
00:14:15,220 --> 00:14:16,460
Little dispute?

308
00:14:17,460 --> 00:14:18,820
Your master's pretty forgiving.

309
00:14:23,540 --> 00:14:24,300
Zhang Dalu.

310
00:14:24,300 --> 00:14:24,940
From Tianjin.

311
00:14:25,020 --> 00:14:25,904
Thirty-two years old.

312
00:14:26,060 --> 00:14:27,280
His original surname was Gao.

313
00:14:27,300 --> 00:14:29,300
Two years ago,

314
00:14:29,300 --> 00:14:30,940
he became the last disciple

315
00:14:30,940 --> 00:14:32,260
of the previous Ironman Zhang

316
00:14:32,780 --> 00:14:34,100
and took the surname Zhang.

317
00:14:35,700 --> 00:14:37,900
Master Hu's newest concubine,
Gao Yingying,

318
00:14:37,900 --> 00:14:38,860
is from the same village.

319
00:14:40,100 --> 00:14:41,260
They were childhood friends.

320
00:14:43,260 --> 00:14:45,180
Who's this Master Hu?

321
00:14:47,420 --> 00:14:48,140
Hu Mingwu.

322
00:14:48,700 --> 00:14:49,980
He claims to be a calligrapher.

323
00:14:50,540 --> 00:14:51,780
A calligrapher?

324
00:14:52,340 --> 00:14:54,220
His handwriting's worse than yours.

325
00:14:58,384 --> 00:14:59,500
Was that a compliment?

326
00:15:06,060 --> 00:15:07,380
Take it however you like.

327
00:15:08,980 --> 00:15:09,580
Thanks.

328
00:15:10,208 --> 00:15:12,180
His father was an official
in the Qing dynasty,

329
00:15:12,180 --> 00:15:14,550
and his younger brother is a chief
at the Ordnance Department.

330
00:15:14,660 --> 00:15:15,820
With that kind of background,

331
00:15:16,260 --> 00:15:19,060
is it that easy to ruin
an ordinary street performer?

332
00:15:19,900 --> 00:15:21,420
Money talks.

333
00:15:21,820 --> 00:15:23,700
When the rich want
to make your life miserable,

334
00:15:23,860 --> 00:15:25,168
they've got plenty of ways.

335
00:15:26,820 --> 00:15:28,660
You should know that well.

336
00:15:35,660 --> 00:15:36,900
Have I ever made trouble for you?

337
00:15:40,580 --> 00:15:42,340
I'll take that as a compliment, too.

338
00:15:43,380 --> 00:15:44,060
Thanks.

339
00:15:47,222 --> 00:15:47,662
Chief.

340
00:15:51,940 --> 00:15:52,540
Chief Yuan.

341
00:15:52,624 --> 00:15:53,616
Young Master Zhao.

342
00:15:53,700 --> 00:15:55,820
My master's calling me back.

343
00:15:59,232 --> 00:16:00,592
Aren't you questioning Douding?

344
00:16:00,780 --> 00:16:01,460
No.

345
00:16:08,700 --> 00:16:09,632
Sorry to bother you.

346
00:16:14,660 --> 00:16:16,020
Are we taking this case?

347
00:16:17,420 --> 00:16:18,380
Why wouldn't we?

348
00:16:19,980 --> 00:16:21,020
There's no victim.

349
00:16:21,300 --> 00:16:22,500
Didn't Zhang Dalu die?

350
00:16:22,660 --> 00:16:24,000
His cause of death is suspicious.

351
00:16:25,180 --> 00:16:26,500
He only faked his death.

352
00:16:26,500 --> 00:16:27,340
He's hiding.

353
00:16:27,660 --> 00:16:29,460
Even if he faked it,

354
00:16:30,020 --> 00:16:31,380
why did he go looking for Douding?

355
00:16:31,660 --> 00:16:32,780
He could've just run away.

356
00:16:35,980 --> 00:16:36,780
Good point.

357
00:16:39,660 --> 00:16:41,540
(Zhang Cong)
What's going on, Master Hu?

358
00:16:41,860 --> 00:16:42,740
(Hu Mingwu)

359
00:16:42,740 --> 00:16:43,580
Master Hu.

360
00:16:43,900 --> 00:16:46,460
- My son!
- My son!

361
00:16:46,860 --> 00:16:49,620
Why did you die so young?

362
00:16:49,620 --> 00:16:51,380
(Mourning)
If we don't open the coffin,

363
00:16:51,620 --> 00:16:52,460
how do we know

364
00:16:52,460 --> 00:16:54,460
your son's really inside?

365
00:16:54,460 --> 00:16:57,220
You bullied my son when he was alive.

366
00:16:57,220 --> 00:17:00,180
Now you want to open his coffin, too?

367
00:17:00,420 --> 00:17:01,210
I'm only thinking

368
00:17:01,220 --> 00:17:03,100
of you two.

369
00:17:03,100 --> 00:17:05,500
You came all the way from Tianjin

370
00:17:05,500 --> 00:17:06,860
to bury him in the family cemetery.

371
00:17:06,860 --> 00:17:08,300
But what if

372
00:17:08,300 --> 00:17:10,180
it's someone else's body inside?

373
00:17:10,180 --> 00:17:12,180
Wouldn't that disgrace
your ancestors?

374
00:17:12,500 --> 00:17:12,980
You!

375
00:17:12,980 --> 00:17:13,780
Master Hu,

376
00:17:13,780 --> 00:17:17,220
I watched the coffin
being sealed myself.

377
00:17:17,220 --> 00:17:18,660
Surely it's not too much

378
00:17:18,660 --> 00:17:20,740
to let his parents

379
00:17:20,740 --> 00:17:22,060
see him one last time.

380
00:17:23,220 --> 00:17:24,380
Master Hu

381
00:17:24,740 --> 00:17:25,860
has a point.

382
00:17:27,340 --> 00:17:28,660
Over my dead body!

383
00:17:29,140 --> 00:17:30,740
If anyone dares open that coffin,

384
00:17:30,740 --> 00:17:31,980
I...

385
00:17:33,580 --> 00:17:35,260
I'll fight you to the death!

386
00:17:35,260 --> 00:17:36,220
If you won't let me

387
00:17:36,220 --> 00:17:37,860
see Dalu off properly

388
00:17:37,860 --> 00:17:39,780
today,

389
00:17:39,780 --> 00:17:40,540
then I'm not leaving

390
00:17:40,540 --> 00:17:42,220
this courtyard.

391
00:17:42,220 --> 00:17:42,940
Open the coffin!

392
00:17:42,940 --> 00:17:44,740
- You can't!
- No!

393
00:17:46,180 --> 00:17:47,540
Don't open it!

394
00:17:47,540 --> 00:17:48,100
Stop!

395
00:17:48,100 --> 00:17:49,780
- Don't open it!
- Don't open it!

396
00:17:50,670 --> 00:17:51,340
Don't open it!

397
00:17:51,340 --> 00:17:52,060
Calm down.

398
00:17:54,780 --> 00:17:57,620
Don't open it!

399
00:17:59,664 --> 00:18:00,816
It really is Zhang Dalu.

400
00:18:00,860 --> 00:18:01,300
Master,

401
00:18:01,300 --> 00:18:01,860
look!

402
00:18:02,060 --> 00:18:02,820
Honey...

403
00:18:12,740 --> 00:18:15,180
(South City
Chinese and Western Medicine Clinic)

404
00:18:20,980 --> 00:18:23,860
(Medical and Surgical Care for All Ages)

405
00:18:23,860 --> 00:18:26,820
(South City
Chinese and Western Medicine Clinic)

406
00:18:33,260 --> 00:18:34,220
Got a lighter?

407
00:18:50,460 --> 00:18:52,780
(End of Episode 24)

408
00:18:55,160 --> 00:18:56,800
♪Side by side,
we journey through this life♪

409
00:18:56,800 --> 00:18:58,340
♪Troubled times
are but a laughing matter♪

410
00:18:58,340 --> 00:18:59,590
♪However, the world changes♪

411
00:18:59,590 --> 00:19:01,510
♪You'll still be by my side♪

412
00:19:01,510 --> 00:19:03,200
♪Side by side,
we journey through this life♪

413
00:19:03,200 --> 00:19:04,770
♪Praise and blame come and go♪

414
00:19:04,770 --> 00:19:06,340
♪If this is my final chapter♪

415
00:19:06,340 --> 00:19:08,840
♪I'll solve this mystery with you♪
